# Architecture & Documentation

The official documentation for Flotter is located in the `docs/` directory.

## Core Documents

- **System Overview**: `docs/architecture/01-system-overview.md`
- **Feature Specification**: `docs/architecture/02-feature-spec.md`
- **Database Schema**: `docs/architecture/03-database-schema.md`

## Directory Map

- `apps/app`: Frontend (Vite + React + TanStack Router)
  - `src/features/`: Client Feature 코드
- `apps/server`: Backend (NestJS + Fastify)
  - Imports from `@repo/features`
- `packages/features`: Server Feature 코드
  - `{name}/server/`: Server-side implementation
- `packages/core`: Shared infrastructure
- `registry`: Feature metadata

## Documentation Structure

- `docs/architecture/`: **Single Source of Truth** for system design & implementation patterns.
- `docs/guides/`: Step-by-step guides (Installation, Testing, Agent Checklist).
- `.claude/rules/`: Coding standards (Frontend, Backend, Imports).
- `docs/templates/`: Standard templates for Issues and READMEs.

## Rules

Always refer to `.claude/rules/frontend/naming-structure.md` or `.claude/rules/backend/naming-dto.md` for naming conventions.
